==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gonochorism
<hw>Gon`o*cho"rism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
offspring + <?/ to separate.]</ety> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Separation of the
sexes in different individuals; -- opposed to
<xex>hermaphroditism</xex>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>In ontogony,
differentiation of male and female individuals from embryos having the
same rudimentary sexual organs.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>In phylogeny,
the evolution of distinct sexes in species previously hermaphrodite or
sexless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gonococcus</ent>⟦br⟧
